    "For example, in Principal-Agent Problems [131], where agents represent principals in performing certain tasks, conflicts of interest arise between the dual objectives of the agent and principal due to information asymmetry.",
    "These are not covered in RLHF fine-tuning.",
    "Moreover, such human-centered approaches may rely on human feedback, which can sometimes be fundamentally flawed or incorrect.",
    "In such cases, AI agents are prone to sycophancy [129].-Sycophancy.",
    "Sycophancy refers to the tendency of LLMs to produce answers that correspond to the beliefs or misleading prompts provided by users, conveyed through suggestive preferences in human feedback during the training process [136]."
